<p>GDP growth: 8.0% GDP: $30bn ($101bn) Inflation: 12.5% Population: 76.2m GDP per head: $390 (PPP: $1,320)</p>

<p>Meles Zenawi, the prime minister, heads a coalition government with a legislative monopoly and will work to tighten his grip ahead of the 2015 elections. Foreign policy will remain tricky, given conflict with Eritrea over borders, intervention in Somalia, water politics with Egypt and peace-keeping between newly created South Sudan and the country from which it seceded. The authorities will struggle to contain inflation in a continuing growth spurt.</p>

